    • Method Detail

      • implement

        public void implement​(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Description copied from interface: Impler
        Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

        Generated class classes name should be same as classes name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

        Specified by:
        implement in interface Impler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        root - root directory.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

      • implementJar

        public void implementJar​(Class<?> token,
                         Path jarFile)
                  throws ImplerException
        Produces .jar file implementing class or interface specified by provided token. Generated class full name should be same as full name of the type token with Impl suffix added. During implementation creates temporary folder to store temporary .java and .class files. If program fails to delete temporary folder, it informs user about it.
        Specified by:
        implementJar in interface JarImpler
        Parameters:
        token - as Class to implement
        jarFile - as Path output .jar file path
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if the given class cannot be generated for one of such reasons:
        • Some arguments are null
        • Error occurs during implementation via implement(Class, Path)
        • JavaCompiler failed to compile implemented class
        • The problems with I/O occurred during implementation.
